title: Grateful Dead Live at Red Rocks Amphitheatre on 1983-09-06
lineage: Sony TC-D5M (original record deck) > Pre Sonus Inspire GT > Sound Forge > .wav files > Trader's Little Helper > flac and ffp files
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway > Greatest Story Ever Told, Peggy-O, Hell In A Bucket, Dupree's Diamond Blues, Minglewood Blues, Bird Song, Lazy Lightning > Supplication > Might As Well

Set 2

Help On The Way > Slipknot! > Franklin's Tower > Playin' In The Band > Drums > Uncle John's Band > Playin' In The Band > Throwing Stones > Not Fade Away 

E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: twards the end of along summer tour. Went to these shows.The sound quality isant even close.But brings back great memories.

Jerry & Bobby guitar duet I think the other aud source has a tinty distorted sound and this one sounds really great.

The Space from this show is a pinnacle example of how Jerry and Bobby's guitar playing progressed in the 1980's. A sweet gooey noodle guitar duet.

They tease Uncle John's and then go back into the jam before going back into Uncle John's. Awesome. And this aud source is super clean.

Stay with it and you'll be delighted This version of the show starts off with Jerry singing from a phone booth sound, but things quickly improve, and then it does some justice to this great show.

We were there whilst on honeymoon in the Rockies and had a great time!
